<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-11-15T15:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-11-15T15:36:00-05:00" n="1211" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1211">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File. No. 812.00/5502.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Consul at Vera
                                    Cruz</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Extract.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Vera Cruz</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-11-15T14:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 15, 1912—2 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Large rebel forces in the northern, numerous small bands in the central
                            and southern part of the State which will scatter all directions on the
                            approach of Federals.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Canada.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>